    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Motley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Vienna</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 22, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatches Nos. 10, 11, 12, 13, and 14.</p>
                <p>I have to report that the relations of this legation with the imperial royal
                    government continue to be of the most satisfactory and cordial nature.</p>
                <p>The steady and victorious progress of our arms in suppressing the mutiny against
                    the United States government commands the entire sympathy of all classes in this
                    country, and is especially hailed with delight by the most liberal organs of the
                    daily press. For political information I beg to refer you to my private letter
                    of this day’s date.</p>
                <p>I remain, most respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. LOTHROP MOTLEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
